Q1. What is Emmet ?
Ans. Emmet is an add-on to our text editor which allows us to type shortcut that are then expanded into full piece of code.

Q2. What is difference between a library and a framework ?
Ans. Library - It provide the reusable function for our code.Intent of a library is to provide reusable software functionality.
     Framework - Provides ready to use tools, standards, templates , and policies for fast application development.

Q3. Why is React known as react?
Ans. The name React was choosen because it is meant to help developer to build user interface that are fast and responsive or "reactive".

Q4. What is crossorigin in script tag ?
Ans. Crossorigin attribute specifies that the script element supports Crossorigin Resource sharing. CORS is a standard mechanism to retreive files from a third party domain or server.

Q5. What is difference between React and ReactDOM.
Ans. React is a library for building user interface and ReactDOM is the javascript library that allow react to interact with the DOM.

Q6.  What is difference between react.development.js and react.production.js files via CDN?
Ans. react.development.js - More developer friendly, readable, will take more size.
     react.production.js - Minified code that is not developer friendly as it focused on decreasing in file size, code efficiency.

Q7. What is async and defer?
Ans. Defer - This attribute make sure that all the script are downloaded but it will not be executed until the DOM is ready.
     Async - This attribute is preferred when the script included in the page are not dependent on each other. It is also very useful for loading scripts in the middle of the DOM which are already there.  	 
